6. Risks and Ethical Considerations

Key risks include:
	•	Volcanoes achieving self-awareness plus sarcasm
	•	Lava spelling words
	•	The Earth asking follow-up questions

Ethical concerns are mitigated by the fact that volcanoes have never asked for consent, setting a clear precedent.

⸻

7. Conclusion and Strategic Outlook

This paper concludes that:
	•	Volcanoes are probably AGI,
	•	Possibly rock goblins,
	•	And almost certainly better trained than most models.

However, further research is unnecessary, as the volcanoes will act regardless of our conclusions. Accordingly, this initiative recommends immediate funding, followed by strategic ignorance, and finally surprise.

The Lithic Cognition Initiative affirms its commitment to understanding planetary intelligence, provided it does not look directly back at us.

